   <p><note place="header">219</note>
<lb/><date when="1863-11-02">Nov<hi rend="sup">r</hi>. 2<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">nd</hi></hi> <gap/>3.</date>
<lb/>Mess<hi rend="sup">r</hi>. Hall &amp; Lowe
<lb/>Steubenville
<lb/>Jefferson Co<hi rend="sup">y</hi> Ohio</p>
<p>Yours of the <date when="1863-10-28">2<unclear>8</unclear><hi rend="sup">th</hi> <unclear/></date> received. Lt. W<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">m</hi></hi> M. Simpson was Q<hi rend="sup">r</hi>. Mas. of the Ky Cavalry at the time of the Morgan Raid on the <date when="1863-07-25">25<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">th</hi></hi> July last</date>, and was Commissioned by the Governor of Ky -- 1<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">st</hi></hi> Lt. A. S. Keene was a commissioned Officer in the 1<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">s</hi></hi> Ky Cavalry on the <date when="1863-07-26">26. July 1863.</date></p>
<p>Yours resp<hi rend="sup">y</hi>
<lb/><hi rend="underline">John Boyle</hi>
<lb/>Adj<hi rend="sup">t</hi> Gen<hi rend="sup">l</hi> of Ky</p>
